Comments:
The only comment I have is that I dont think of people in terms of their grouping, by skin tone or any other grouping. I see people as individuals . That fact made it difficult for me to answer the questions regarding my feelings (warm to cold) of groups of people. I think of people in terms of their own character, the way they are, no matter to what group they belong. 

Even though I have many friends who are married to someone of a different group (as defined in this survey), I had a hard time trying to recall them because, as I said, I think of people as people, not as members of a particular group. I never saw the couples as being of two different groups. In other words, I dont think of people as black or white. I think of them as human beings of good or bad character. If the survey had asked me my feelings towards people, of good or bad character, there wouldve been a huge difference in the thermostat readings.
